fixes theta :: real
assumes h0 : "tan theta = (cos (5 * pi / 180) * cos (20 * pi / 180) + cos (35 * pi / 180) * cos (50 * pi / 180) - sin (5 * pi / 180) * sin (20 * pi / 180) - sin (35 * pi / 180) * sin (50 * pi / 180)) / (sin (5 * pi / 180) * cos (20 * pi / 180) - sin (35 * pi / 180) * cos (50 * pi / 180) + cos (5 * pi / 180) * sin (20 * pi / 180) - cos (35 * pi / 180) * sin (50 * pi / 180))"
shows  "theta = 120 * pi / 180"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Find the degree measure of the least positive angle $\theta$ for which
\[\tan \theta = \frac{\cos 5^\circ \cos 20^\circ + \cos 35^\circ \cos 50^\circ - \sin 5^\circ \sin 20^\circ - \sin 35^\circ \sin 50^\circ}{\sin 5^\circ \cos 20^\circ - \sin 35^\circ \cos 50^\circ + \cos 5^\circ \sin 20^\circ - \cos 35^\circ \sin 50^\circ}.\] The final Answer is 120^\circ
 ### Proof
 From the angle addition formula, the numerator is \begin{align} &(\cos 5^\circ \cos 20^\circ - \sin 5^\circ \sin 20^\circ) + (\cos 35^\circ \cos 50^\circ -  \sin 35^\circ \sin 50^\circ) \\ &= \cos (5^\circ + 20^\circ) + \cos (35^\circ + 50^\circ) \\
 &= \cos 25^\circ + \cos 85^\circ. \end{align}From the sum-to-product formula, $\cos 25^\circ + \cos 85^\circ = 2 \cos 55^\circ \cos 30^\circ.$
 Similarly, the denominator is \begin{align} &\sin 5^\circ \cos 20^\circ - \sin 35^\circ \cos 50^\circ + \cos 5^\circ \sin 20^\circ - \cos 35^\circ \sin 50^\circ) \\ &= (\sin 5^\circ \cos 20^\circ +  \cos 5^\circ \sin 20^\circ) - (\sin 35^\circ \cos 50^\circ + \cos 35^\circ \sin 50^\circ) \\
 &= \sin (5^\circ + 20^\circ) - \sin (35^\circ + 50^\circ) \\ &= \sin 25^\circ - \sin 85^\circ \\ &= -2 \sin 30^\circ \cos 55^\circ, \end{align}so the expression is equal to \[\frac{2 \cos 55^\circ \cos 30^\circ}{-2 \sin 30^\circ \cos 55^\circ} = -\frac{\cos 30^\circ}{\sin 30^\circ} = -\sqrt{3} = \tan 120^\circ.\]Hence, the smallest such $\theta$ is $\boxed{120^\circ}.$
 *)

assumes h0 : "tan theta = (cos (5 * pi / 180) * cos (20 * pi / 180) + cos (35 * pi / 180) * cos (50 * pi / 180) - sin (5 * pi / 180) * sin (20 * pi / 180) - sin (35 * pi / 180) * sin (50 * pi / 180)) / (sin (5 * pi / 180) * cos (20 * pi / 180) - sin (35 * pi / 180) * cos (50 * pi / 180) + cos (5 * pi / 180) * sin (20 * pi / 180) - cos (35 * pi / 180) * sin (50 * pi / 180))"
shows  "theta = 120 * pi / 180"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_7.informal problem: Find the angle $\theta$ such that its tangent equals the expression $\frac{(cos(5\pi/180)cos(20\pi/180) + cos(35\pi/180)cos(50\pi/180) - sin(5\pi/180)sin(20\pi/180) - sin(35\pi/180)sin(50\pi/180))}{(sin(5\pi/180)cos(20\pi/180) - sin(35\pi/180)cos(50\pi/180) + cos(5\pi/180)sin(20\pi/180) - cos(35\pi/180)sin(50\pi/180))}$. The answer is $\theta = 120\pi/180$.

a_8.formal problem:
theorem
fixes theta :: real
assumes h0 : "tan theta = (cos (5 * pi / 180) * cos (20 * pi / 180) + cos (35 * pi / 180) * cos (50 * pi / 180) - sin (5 * pi / 180) * sin (20 * pi / 180) - sin (35 * pi / 180) * sin (50 * pi / 180)) / (sin (5 * pi / 180) * cos (20 * pi / 180) - sin (35 * pi / 180) * cos (50 * pi / 180) + cos (5 * pi / 180) * sin (20 * pi / 180) - cos (35 * pi / 180) * sin (50 * pi / 180))"
and h1 : "theta > 0"
shows  "theta = 120 * pi / 180"
a_8.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Find the degree measure of the least positive angle $\theta$ for which
\[\tan \theta = \frac{\cos 5^\circ \cos 20^\circ + \cos 35^\circ \cos 50^\circ - \sin 5^\circ \sin 20^\circ - \sin 35^\circ \sin 50^\circ}{\sin 5^\circ \cos 20^\circ - \sin 35^\circ \cos 50^\circ + \cos 5^\circ \sin 20^\circ - \cos 35^\circ \sin 50^\circ}.\] The final Answer is 120^\circ
 ### Proof
 From the angle addition formula, the numerator is \begin{align} &(\cos 5^\circ \cos 20^\circ - \sin 5^\circ \sin 20^\circ) + (\cos 35^\circ \cos 50^\circ -  \sin 35^\circ \sin 50^\circ) \\ &= \cos (5^\circ + 20^\circ) + \cos (35^\circ + 50^\circ) \\
 &= \cos 25^\circ + \cos 85^\circ. \end{align}From the sum-to-product formula, $\cos 25^\circ + \cos 85^\circ = 2 \cos 55^\circ \cos 30^\circ.$
 Similarly, the denominator is \begin{align} &\sin 5^\circ \cos 20^\circ - \sin 35^\circ \cos 50^\circ + \cos 5^\circ \sin 20^\circ - \cos 35^\circ \sin 50^\circ) \\ &= (\sin 5^\circ \cos 20^\circ +  \cos 5^\circ \sin 20^\circ) - (\sin 35^\circ \cos 50^\circ + \cos 35^\circ \sin 50^\circ) \\
 &= \sin (5^\circ + 20^\circ) - \sin (35^\circ + 50^\circ) \\ &= \sin 25^\circ - \sin 85^\circ \\ &= -2 \sin 30^\circ \cos 55^\circ, \end{align}so the expression is equal to \[\frac{2 \cos 55^\circ \cos 30^\circ}{-2 \sin 30^\circ \cos 55^\circ} = -\frac{\cos 30^\circ}{\sin 30^\circ} = -\sqrt{3} = \tan 120^\circ.\]Hence, the smallest such $\theta$ is $\boxed{120^\circ}.$
 *)
